Issue Summary 

The deployment includes both Vlocity and Salesforce components, and a number of these components depend on one another. Because of these dependencies, deployment and activation must be split into multiple PRs and executed in the correct order. 

Key Dependencies Identified 

FlexCard activation is required before OmniScript activation 
OmniScripts that reference FlexCards can only be activated after the dependent FlexCards are activated. 

FlexCard activation sequence must be followed 
Some FlexCards depend on other FlexCards, so the activation order is important. 

FlexCard activation depends on LWC availability in the org 
If a FlexCard references an LWC, that LWC must already be present in the target org before the FlexCard can be activated. 

FlexCard activation depends on OmniScript availability in the org 
If a FlexCard references an OmniScript, the OmniScript must already exist and be active in the org. 

Apex classes depend on Expression Sets and Decision Matrices 
Apex classes that use these artifacts cannot function correctly unless the related Expression Sets and Decision Matrices are already deployed. 

LWC and Flow that references the same LWC cannot be deployed together 
This creates deployment conflicts, so these components must be separated into different PRs. 

 

